This paper deals with the problem of distributed control of large-scale networked nonlinear dynamic systems, which is a topic in the field of control systems (cs.SY). The paper also proposes a method for synthesizing controllers based on SDP decompositions, which is a technique commonly used in optimization and machine learning (cs.MA). The paper also discusses the application of the proposed method to vehicle platooning, which is a topic in robotics (cs.RO). Additionally, the paper uses pointwise linear matrix inequalities, which is a technique used in linear algebra and optimization, and the paper proposes a method for systems on chordal graphs, which is a topic in graph theory and network science. These topics suggest that the paper could also be relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and network science (cs.NE).
